bug.short_desc: Resource Managment is not longer working

long_desc.thetext:
Created attachment 1307 new generated test project
Hello,
the resource managment is not longer working. I can't find the Location.
I appended a new generated application and changed the button to
var button1 = new qx.ui.form.Button("First Button", "icon/16/actions/help-about.png");
After generate build and running the application the requested button address is http://localhost:8080/qx/icon/Tango/16/actions/help-about.png.
Should be http://localhost:8080/resource/qx/icon/Tango/16/actions/help-about.png
Any idea what has happened?
In svn version 61647 everything works correct.
Best regards Henner Kollmann
Thanks for the report. We will check whats wrong here.

The resource Manager is working correct. The icons are not mentioned in the generated resource list.
Could this be the same problem as http://bugzilla.qooxdoo.org/show_bug.cgi?id=8107 ?

Hi Henner,
you need an additional asset hint in your Application.js:
* @asset(qx/icon/Tango/16/actions/help-about.png)
because otherwise the Generator won't copy that file into "build/resource/..." and also won't register its resource id.
It probably worked in former times because of bug #7045, comment 11.

Oh and maybe this manual page helps:
http://manual.qooxdoo.org/3.5/pages/desktop/ui_resources.html
Feel free to reopen if I missed something. :)

Sorry,
seems that my application depends on an - now fixed - qooxdoo bug.
best regards, Henner
